SLOW COOKER CHICKEN FAJITAS
http://backtoherroots.com/2015/10/15/slow-cooker-chicken-fajitas/
PREP TIME: 10 mins
COOK TIME: 6 hours
4 SERVINGS

1 cup salsa
1 pound chicken breasts, sliced into thin strips
1 each Pero Family Farms red, yellow, and green pepper, sliced into thin strips
1 large onion, sliced into thin strips
4 cloves garlic, minced
2 tablespoons chili powder
2 tablespoons cumin
1 teaspoon paprika
1 teaspoon salt
1/4 cup lime juice
1 tablespoon honey
Tortillas, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, avocados, olives, etc. for serving

Pour the salsa into the basin of a slow cooker. Top with the chicken, peppers,
onions, and garlic.

In a small bowl, whisk together the chili powder, cumin, paprika, salt, lime
juice and honey. Pour over the chicken mixture.

Place lid on slow cooker, and cook on low for 6 hours or high for 4. Use a
slotted spoon to remove the veggies and chicken and serve on warm tortillas
with your favorite toppings.
